## 1.2 Detailed Transaction Flow

### Step 1: Manufacturer Creates Batch

```
Manufacturer opens app
    â†“
Logs in with Ethereum wallet (MetaMask)
    â†“
Clicks "Create Batch"
    â†“
Fills form:
â”œâ”€ Product name
â”œâ”€ Quantity
â”œâ”€ Expiry date
â”œâ”€ Manufacturing date
â””â”€ Storage temperature
    â†“
Backend generates:
â”œâ”€ Batch ID (auto)
â”œâ”€ Unique serial numbers (one per unit)
â””â”€ QR codes (one per unit, contains serial + batch ID)
    â†“
Smart contract executes:
â”œâ”€ Creates Block #1: BatchCreated
â”œâ”€ Stores on blockchain
â”œâ”€ Makes immutable
â””â”€ Returns transaction hash
    â†“
Frontend displays:
â”œâ”€ Success confirmation
â”œâ”€ Batch ID
â”œâ”€ QR codes (downloadable)
â”œâ”€ Transaction hash
â””â”€ Blockchain explorer link
    â†“
Database saves:
â”œâ”€ Batch metadata (MongoDB)
â”œâ”€ QR code images (AWS S3)
â””â”€ Blockchain reference
```

### Step 2: Manufacturer Assigns to Distributor

```
Manufacturer clicks "Assign to Distributor"
    â†“
Selects distributor from list
    â†“
Confirms quantity & details
    â†“
Backend creates Block #2: BatchTransferred
â”œâ”€ From: Manufacturer address
â”œâ”€ To: Distributor address
â”œâ”€ Amount: Batch quantity
â””â”€ Status: ASSIGNED_TO_DISTRIBUTOR
    â†“
Notification sent to Distributor:
â”œâ”€ Email: "New batch assigned to you"
â”œâ”€ Dashboard alert: "Pending acceptance"
â””â”€ SMS (optional)
    â†“
Status on blockchain: ASSIGNED (immutable)
```

### Step 3: Distributor Accepts Batch

```
Distributor logs in
    â†“
Sees "Pending Acceptance" section
    â†“
Clicks "Accept Batch" button
    â†“
Form appears with:
â”œâ”€ Batch details (read-only)
â”œâ”€ Warehouse selection (dropdown)
â”œâ”€ Temperature settings
â”œâ”€ Physical verification checklist
â”œâ”€ Receipt upload
â””â”€ Digital signature
    â†“
Backend validates form
    â†“
Smart contract executes:
â”œâ”€ Creates Block #3: DistributorAcceptedBatch
â”œâ”€ Changes ownership: Manufacturer â†’ Distributor
â”œâ”€ Updates status: AT_DISTRIBUTOR
â””â”€ Records timestamp
    â†“
Database updates:
â”œâ”€ Inventory table: Batch added to distributor warehouse
â”œâ”€ Ownership tracking: New owner recorded
â””â”€ Metadata: Receipt + photos stored
    â†“
Frontend shows:
â”œâ”€ Success notification
â”œâ”€ Batch moved to "In Warehouse" section
â”œâ”€ [Create Shipment] button now visible
â””â”€ Block confirmation with details
```

### Step 4: Distributor Creates Shipment

```
Distributor clicks "Create Shipment"
    â†“
Multi-step form appears:
â”œâ”€ Select batches to ship (checkboxes)
â”œâ”€ Select destination pharmacy
â”œâ”€ Enter packaging details
â”œâ”€ Select transporter
â”œâ”€ Assign vehicle & driver
â””â”€ Set delivery SLA
    â†“
Backend validates:
â”œâ”€ Pharmacy is authorized (license check)
â”œâ”€ Transporter has insurance
â”œâ”€ Vehicle is certified
â””â”€ Inventory is sufficient
    â†“
Smart contract creates Block #4: ShipmentCreatedByDistributor
â”œâ”€ Shipment ID (auto-generated)
â”œâ”€ Batches included
â”œâ”€ Destination details
â”œâ”€ Transporter info
â”œâ”€ SLA details
â””â”€ Status: PENDING_PICKUP
    â†“
Notification system:
â”œâ”€ Email to Transporter: "Ready for pickup"
â”œâ”€ SMS alert: "New shipment SHIP-202412-001"
â””â”€ Dashboard task: "Pending Pickups"
    â†“
Batch status: PENDING_PICKUP (awaiting transporter)
```

### Step 5: Transporter Picks Up Shipment

```
Transporter logs in
    â†“
Sees "Pending Pickups" list
    â†“
Clicks [Pickup] button
    â†“
Verification form appears:
â”œâ”€ Scan QR codes (verify seals)
â”œâ”€ Confirm package count
â”œâ”€ Record pickup time & location (GPS auto-filled)
â”œâ”€ Take photos
â””â”€ Driver signature
    â†“
