## 4.3 No Separate Chains Per Company

### Why NOT Separate Chains?

```
âŒ WRONG APPROACH: Separate chain per company

Company A Chain:
â”œâ”€ Batch B-001
â”œâ”€ Shipment S-001
â””â”€ Isolated from other companies

Company B Chain:
â”œâ”€ Batch B-002
â”œâ”€ Shipment S-002
â””â”€ Isolated from other companies

PROBLEMS:
âœ— No cross-company transparency
âœ— Batches can't transfer between companies
âœ— Can't verify end-to-end journey
âœ— Each company controls their own chain (defeats purpose)
âœ— Counterfeiters can fake an entire company chain
âœ— Expensive (operate multiple blockchain networks)
```

### âœ… CORRECT APPROACH: Single Shared Chain

```
Single Unified Blockchain:

Block #1: Cipla creates batch B-001
â”œâ”€ Actor: Cipla address
â”œâ”€ Status: CREATED
â””â”€ Immutable record

Block #2: Cipla transfers to MotilalOswal
â”œâ”€ Actor: Cipla address
â”œâ”€ To: MotilalOswal address
â”œâ”€ Status: ASSIGNED
â””â”€ Immutable record

Block #3: MotilalOswal accepts batch
â”œâ”€ Actor: MotilalOswal address
â”œâ”€ Status: AT_DISTRIBUTOR
â””â”€ Immutable record

Block #4: MotilalOswal ships via FastHaul
â”œâ”€ Actor: MotilalOswal address
â”œâ”€ Transporter: FastHaul address
â”œâ”€ Status: IN_TRANSIT
â””â”€ Immutable record

Block #5-10: FastHaul logs temperatures
â”œâ”€ Actor: FastHaul address
â”œâ”€ Multiple entries
â”œâ”€ Status: IN_TRANSIT
â””â”€ Immutable records

Block #11: FastHaul delivers to City Pharmacy
â”œâ”€ Actor: FastHaul address
â”œâ”€ Delivered to: City Pharmacy
â”œâ”€ Status: DELIVERY_COMPLETED
â””â”€ Immutable record

Block #12: City Pharmacy accepts
â”œâ”€ Actor: City Pharmacy address
â”œâ”€ Status: AT_PHARMACY (ownership transferred)
â””â”€ Immutable record

Block #13: Pharmacy dispenses to customer
â”œâ”€ Actor: Pharmacy address
â”œâ”€ Patient: Hashed ID
â”œâ”€ Status: DISPENSED
â””â”€ Immutable record

PUBLIC VERIFICATION (No login needed):
Scan QR code â†’ See ALL blocks #1-13
â†’ Full transparency from manufacturer to patient
```

